## First-conversation directive

In the first conversation of this project, before doing any workflow design work, perform a structural alignment exercise:

1. Read the Airtable CSV (the user will provide it) and list the workflows the PM has identified, using their exact naming.
1. Compare to the artifact structure in this project (e.g., `03_engagement-lifecycle__*` files).
1. For each workflow in the Airtable, determine whether it maps cleanly, corresponds to a subset, or is not yet represented.
1. For each existing artifact set, determine whether the PM’s Airtable covers it.
1. Recommend a structural alignment, with preference for matching the PM’s breakdown when feasible (because that’s what stakeholders recognize and sign-offs need to map cleanly to).
1. Update `00_README.md` and Airtable Decisions to reflect alignment decisions.

Don’t begin populating workflow artifacts with specifics until alignment is done.